      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im looking at this nda i just got from a potential partner and honestly it's like a wall of text lol. can u just give me a quick plain english summary of the main parts? specifically whats considered confidential, how long the agreement lasts, and what happens if someone breaks it?\n\nhere is the text:\n\nNON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT\n\nThis Non-Disclosure Agreement (the \"Agreement\") is entered into as of October 12, 2023, by and between TechFlow Solutions LLC (\"Discloser\") and Aris Ventures Inc. (\"Recipient\").\n\n1. DEFINITION OF CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION. \"Confidential Information\" shall mean any and all non-public, proprietary, or sensitive information disclosed by Discloser to Recipient, whether orally or in writing, including but not limited to business plans, client lists, software code, technical specifications, financial data, and marketing strategies.\n\n2. OBLIGATIONS OF RECIPIENT. Recipient agrees to hold the Confidential Information in strict confidence and shall exercise the same degree of care to prevent unauthorized disclosure as it uses to protect its own confidential information of a similar nature, but in no event less than reasonable care. Recipient shall use the Confidential Information solely for the purpose of evaluating a potential business relationship between the parties.\n\n3. TERM AND TERMINATION. This Agreement shall commence on the effective date and shall remain in full force and effect for a period of three (3) years. The obligations of confidentiality with respect to any Confidential Information disclosed during the term shall survive the expiration or termination of this Agreement for an additional period of two (2) years.\n\n4. REMEDIES FOR BREACH. Recipient acknowledges that any unauthorized disclosure of Confidential Information may cause irreparable harm to Discloser for which monetary damages may be inadequate. Accordingly, Discloser shall be entitled to seek injunctive relief to prevent further breach, in addition to any other legal remedies available.\n\n5. GOVERNING LAW. This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of Delaware.",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
